Upon completion the student has an overview of transcription and notation history and folk music notation traditions in Estonia and elsewhere. As a major issue the specific problems of folk music notation in the fields of vocal and instrumental music are dealt with. Transcription as an ethno music subtype and aid in analysis. Musical listening, attention, memory are developed through practical tasks. Eventually every student has developed their own personal notation technique.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Developing musical literacy, improving musical memory and attention, knowing transcription related issues, developing analyzing skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student can make transkriptions about different traditional instruments and know's  the differences. Know's the history about ancient instruments in the tradition. Can find the archive recordings and know's how to use them.
